From: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
Date: Wed, 8 Feb 2017 21:14:58 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 1779/2066] arm64: dts: r8a7795-salvator-xs: Add CSI2 device
 support

This patch adds CSI2{20,40} device support for Salvator-X 2nd version
board on R8A7795 ES2.0 SoC.

Signed-off-by: Takeshi Kihara <takeshi.kihara.df@renesas.com>
[zou:Original patch taken from
git://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/horms/renesas-bsp.git
 v4.9/rcar-3.5.1]
Signed-off-by: zou cao <cao.zou@windriver.com>
---
 .../arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts |   38 ++++++++++++++++++++
 1 files changed, 38 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts
index d5431aa..dd8aab5 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/renesas/r8a7795-salvator-xs.dts
@@ -655,3 +655,41 @@
 &vin7 {
 	status = "okay";
 };
+
+&csi2_20 {
+	status = "okay";
+
+	ports {
+		#address-cells = <1>;
+		#size-cells = <0>;
+
+		port@0 {
+			reg = <0>;
+
+			csi2_20_0_in: endpoint@0 {
+				clock-lanes = <0>;
+				data-lanes = <1>;
+				virtual-channel-number = <1>;
+			};
+		};
+	};
+};
+
+&csi2_40 {
+	status = "okay";
+
+	ports {
+		#address-cells = <1>;
+		#size-cells = <0>;
+
+		port@0 {
+			reg = <0>;
+
+			csi2_40_0_in: endpoint@0 {
+				clock-lanes = <0>;
+				data-lanes = <1 2 3 4>;
+				virtual-channel-number = <1>;
+			};
+		};
+	};
+};
